config EMUL_TPS25750
    bool "Emulate a TI TPS25750 USB-PD controller (native_sim tests)"
    depends on EMUL && TPS25750
    help
      I2C register-file emulator for the TPS25750 PD controller's host
      interface: the MODE/CMD1/DATA1 4CC task protocol, the I2Cm
      bridge (serving an embedded BQ25792 register file, so the real
      bq25792 driver works unmodified behind the real tps25750 bridge
      driver), and the PBMs/PBMc patch-download flow including the
      secondary patch-port I2C address. Only useful on native_sim; can
      never be enabled in hardware builds because CONFIG_EMUL is off
      there.

config EMUL_TPS25750_BOOT_MODE_PTCH
    bool "Emulated TPS25750 boots in PTCH mode (awaiting patch)"
    depends on EMUL_TPS25750
    default n
    help
      When enabled the emulated part powers up in "PTCH" mode with the
      ReadyForPatch interrupt bit set, so a driver built with
      CONFIG_TPS25750_INTERNAL_PATCH=y performs a full patch download
      during init. When disabled the part boots in "APP " mode (patch
      already loaded), matching proto0's normal EEPROM-booted state.
